Certainly! Here's a basic React.js template for a simple auction marketplace:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';

const AuctionMarketplace = () => {
  // Declare state variables
  const [auctions, setAuctions] = useState([]);
  const [newAuction, setNewAuction] = useState('');

  // Function to handle adding new auctions
  const handleAddAuction = () => {
    if (newAuction.trim().length > 0) {
      setAuctions([...auctions, newAuction]);
      setNewAuction('');
    }
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Auction Marketplace</h1>
      <div>
        <input
          type="text"
          value={newAuction}
          onChange={(e) => setNewAuction(e.target.value)}
        />
        <button onClick={handleAddAuction}>Add Auction</button>
      </div>
      <ul>
        {auctions.map((auction, index) => (
          <li key={index}>{auction}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
};

export default AuctionMarketplace;
```

To use this template, you need to have React.js installed in your project. You can create a new React.js app using `create-react-app`, or add the above component to an existing React.js project.

Please note that this template only includes basic functionality for adding and displaying auctions. Depending on your requirements, you may need to add more features such as bidding, timers, and authentication.

Remember to modify and style the template according to your specific needs and design preferences.
